<div class="row">
	<div class="col-md-6">
		<div class="recipe-modal-img-container">
			<img src="${pageContext.request.contextPath}/recipes/Hearty_Beef_Stew.jpg" />
		</div>
		<h4>Ingredients</h4>
		<ul class="ingredients">
			<li>​1 pound ground beef or stew meat, browned</li>
			<li>2 cups beef or vegetable broth</li>
			<li>1 zucchini, cubed</li>
			<li>​1 large or 3 small kohlrabi, peeled and diced</li>
			<li>8 ounces mushrooms, chopped</li>
			<li>1 pound green beans</li>
			<li>2 large chopped tomatoes or 1 can diced tomatoes</li>
			<li>1 bunch green onions, chopped</li>
			<li>3-4 garlic cloves</li>
			<li>1 bell pepper</li>
			<li>1 package IP Mushroom Soup</li>
			<li>1 tsp each Rosemary, Thy​​​me, onion powder​</li>
			<li>salt and pepper to taste</li>
		</ul>
	</div>
	<div class="col-md-6">
		<h4>Instructions</h4>
		<ol class="instructions">
			<li>In a large pot, add to cooked meat zucchini, kohlrabi, mushrooms, green beans, chopped tomatoes, green onions, bell pepper, and garlic cloves.  Add part of the broth for moisture and simmer on medium heat until vegetables are tender.</li>
			<li>Use the remaining broth to prepare the IP soup (set aside)</li>
			<li>When vegetables are tender, add the prepared Mushroom Soup and seasonings.</li>
			<li>Simmer an additional 30-60 minutes</li>
		</ol>
	</div>
	
</div>